Hi, and welcome back to Line Sheet, live from Milan, where Sabato De
Sarno wants you to know he is not slinking away. The former Gucci designer =
was out and about this week as anticipation builds about the impending anno=
uncement of his replacement, which is expected sooner than soon.

=C2=A0

In today=E2=80=99s Inner Circle issue, I explore why the search for Sabato=
=E2=80=99s successor is so consequential to the future of Gucci and parentc=
o Kering, but not in the way you might
think. Up top, I have a near-instant report from the Prada show and notes o=
n the Silvia Venturini Fendi rally=E2=80=94and, for a special treat, Sarah =
Shapiro explains how Nuuly used its second-mover advantage to make the clot=
hing rental business model work.

=C2=A0

By the time you read this, I=E2=80=99ll be heading home from a dinner in th=
